cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with scene understanding and semantic segmentation, which are core computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the development of robust models, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of analytic and empirical evidence suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The potential danger involved in interacting with humans suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses the correction of potentially errant non-distinct mappings, which may also fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
